name: Mini Chip Sugar Cookies

name: Melt in your Mouth Cookies II
description: By making your own brown sugar, these cookies will be the chewiest and moistest ones you'll ever make.

name: Honey-butter Biscuit Cookies

name: Chocolate Peanut Butter Squares

name: Brownies I
description: When I make this for friends, I add nuts. When I make this for myself, I add raisins. I've tried M&M candies, toffee bits, and candy confetti -- it's very flexible.

description: My grandmother made these in her woodstove oven and I have always guessed at the cooking temperature and cooking times. As is usual with lots of older recipes no exact amount of flour was listed either.

name: Cereal Treats I

You may use , raisins, chocolate chips, M & M candies or coconut instead of the walnuts if you wish.

name: Oatmeal Raisin Cookies III
description: Oatmeal Raisin Cookie that calls for boilng the raisins. This makes a very delicious moist cookie.
ingredients: 1 cup raisins #1 ¼ cups water #⅔ cup butter #1 cup white sugar #2 eggs #1 cup rolled oats #2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 teaspoon ground cinnamon #½ teaspoon ground cloves #½ teaspoon ground nutmeg #½ teaspoon salt

name: Babe Ruth Bars
description: These taste like the candy bar.
ingredients: 1 cup peanut butter #1 cup white corn syrup #½ cup packed brown sugar #½ cup white sugar #6 cups cornflakes cereal #1 cup semisweet chocolate chips #⅔ cup peanuts

name: Peanut Butter Candy Blossoms
description: Friend gave this to me a long time ago.
ingredients: 1 cup butter, softened #1 cup creamy peanut butter #1 cup packed brown sugar #1 cup white sugar #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #20 fun size bars chocolate-coated caramel-peanut nougat candy

name: Black and White Cookies II
description: Big cookies frosted with half chocolate and half white frosting.
ingredients: 1 ¾ cups white sugar #1 cup unsalted butter #4 eggs #1 ½ cups milk #½ teaspoon vanilla extract #¼ teaspoon lemon extract #2 ½ cups cake flour #2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking powder #½ teaspoon salt #4 cups confectioners' sugar #½ cup boiling water #1 (1 ounce) square bittersweet chocolate #1 teaspoon light corn syrup

name: Cherry Flips
description: Shortbread-like cookie with a cherry tucked in the center. Frost with a tinted buttercream icing.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #2 egg yolks #½ teaspoon salt #½ cup confectioners' sugar #2 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 teaspoons almond extract #36 maraschino cherries #½ cup flaked coconut

name: Irish Potatoes
description: Small, no-bake cookies that look like potatoes. It's fast and easy.
ingredients: 1 cup confectioners' sugar #1 cup shredded coconut #1 ½ tablespoons cream #2 tablespoons ground cinnamon

name: Wookie Cookies
description: Easy and delicious.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 cup white sugar #½ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon baking powder #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #½ cup chopped walnuts #1 cup crisp rice cereal #1 teaspoon vanilla extract

name: Children's Delight Cookies
description: This was a favorite of my 6 children. It is easy to make and if the batch is too large, the recipe is easily cut in half.
ingredients: 2 cups water #3 cups raisins #2 cups shortening #8 cups all-purpose flour #2 teaspoons baking powder #2 teaspoons baking soda #1 teaspoon salt #4 cups white sugar #6 eggs #2 teaspoons vanilla extract #2 teaspoons ground cinnamon

name: Peanut Butter Chip Cookies I
description: Rich cookies with peanut butter chips.
ingredients: 2 cups all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking soda #1 cup butter flavored shortening #1 cup white sugar #½ cup packed brown sugar #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 eggs #1 ⅔ cups peanut butter chips

name: Doubly Delicious Peanut Butter Cookies
description: Chewy and crunchy at the same time, these are the ultimate in peanut butter goodness.
ingredients: 1 cup white sugar #1 cup packed brown sugar #1 cup crunchy peanut butter #½ cup butter flavored shortening #2 eggs #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking soda #¼ teaspoon salt #2 cups peanut butter chips

name: My Favorite Cookie
description: I have played around with this old family recipe adding nuts, chips etc. and it always turns out really good and if made ahead is really quick when you need cookies in a hurry.
ingredients: 1 cup butter #1 tablespoon vanilla extract #1 cup packed brown sugar #1 teaspoon salt #1 cup white sugar #1 teaspoon baking soda #3 ½ cups all-purpose flour #2 eggs #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Black Pepper Cookies
description: Cookies with black pepper.
ingredients: 3 eggs #2 cups packed light brown sugar #2 cups all-purpose flour #½ teaspoon baking soda #½ teaspoon salt #1 teaspoon ground cloves #2 teaspoons ground cinnamon #½ teaspoon ground black pepper #1 cup finely chopped walnuts #2 ½ cups raisins #2 tablespoons chopped candied citron #⅓ cup confectioners' sugar for decoration

name: Chocolate Butterscotch Squares
description: This recipe is so easy - just mix and bake.
ingredients: 1 ½ cups graham cracker crumbs #1 (14 ounce) can sweetened condensed milk #1 cup semisweet chocolate chips #1 cup butterscotch chips #1 cup chopped walnuts

name: Cloud Nine Butterscotch Squares
description: Butterscotch cookie squares with chips.
ingredients: ½ cup butter #1 (3.4 ounce) package instant butterscotch pudding mix #2 eggs #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #1 cup all-purpose flour #1 teaspoon baking powder #½ cup milk #1 cup rolled oats #1 cup semisweet chocolate chips

name: Cow Patty Cookies
description: No bake peanut butter, oat, and nut cookies.
ingredients: 2 cups white sugar #5 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder #½ cup unsalted butter #½ cup crunchy peanut butter #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #3 cups quick cooking oats #½ cup chopped walnuts #½ cup milk

name: No Bake Peanut Butter Cookies II
description: I got this recipe from my Grandmother. They're very easy to make and very good.
ingredients: 1 cup white sugar #1 cup white corn syrup #1 teaspoon vanilla extract #2 cups peanut butter #4 ½ cups crisp rice cereal

name: Langues de Chat
description: These cookies are called 'cat's tongues'. They are easy to make. This is a French recipe, but it has already been converted to conventional measurements.
ingredients: 9 tablespoons butter, softened #½ cup white sugar #2 tablespoons white sugar #3 egg whites #1 ½ teaspoons vanilla extract #1 ½ cups all-purpose flour #6 (1 ounce) squares semisweet chocolate, melted
